#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:137
# 4e079092e5d3483cb6f8f52c0d52b4e2
msgid "The :guilabel:`Building Tool` allows you to create shapes with 90 degree corners with just three clicks.  First, you trace the edge of your building and then you drag out the line to make it a polygon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:147
# a82307cc7c51446db3849fb16b68825d
msgid "You can also create more complicated buildings by using the merge option. Create your building outline, select all of the polygons (press :kbd:`SHIFT` to highlight them all) and then hit :kbd:`SHIFT + J` to merge the objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:154
# 724d9a5ab9bf41cfb0c691c2c28b5487
msgid "Furthermore, you can also change the default settings (size and tagging) on :menuselection:`Data > Set building size`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:160
# f43f402a41d94847973c8057f780ffbf
msgid "If you are dealing with a similar size of building, you can change building in certain dimensions, such as 5 x 6 meter (unit in meter). Furthermore, if you mapping same infrastructure, such as townhouses in same area, you can edit tags on :guilabel:`Advanced` tab that all objects are mapped into same building tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:169
# 321103a84b7143d9bb49523293a08c08
msgid "**Utilsplugin2 (More Tools)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:171
# 6030e769b9b1412ca80ef87e2d0aa572
msgid "The plugin utilsplugin2 has several features that are also useful for editing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:176
# 6beb8bb316d249d296f5a12166c6dbb1
msgid "After you install this plugin, a new menu will appear called :menuselection:`More Tools`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:182
# 5bb89eb0076c4a6bb7fc34f244505e93
msgid "The following tools are generally the most useful:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:184
# fc5f99d6ab844fabb2ea47f464486b8f
msgid "**Add Nodes at Intersections:**  This tool is very helpful for adding missing nodes in intersections of selected ways.  It is good practice that roads and rivers should always have common nodes where they intersect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:191
# e0db378720134c98affe694288b75056
msgid "**Copy Tags from Previous Selection:**  This function makes copying tags easier. If you want to create many objects with the same tags, first draw the objects. Then add the tags to one object. Click on another object and press :kbd:`Shift + R` to copy the tags from the previously selected object. You can do this for all objects that you want to tag. Remember that the tags will be copied from the previously selected object, so if you click on an untagged object and then another untagged object, you will not be able to copy any tags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:203
# 5c41dfb5cf364d6e88081710093636ff
msgid "**Add Source Tag:** This tool simplifies adding a source tag. It remembers the source that was specified last and adds it as remembered source tag to your objects. You can insert the source with just one click."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:207
# 34962ff9ddc9499abee1ff0a8144f991
msgid "**Replace Geometry:** This tool is great if you want to redraw a poorly shaped object, but want to keep the history, attributes and ID number of that object. For example, if you come across a building that is complicated and drawn in a poor fashion, then instead of painfully changing each node, you can (2) just draw the object again (3) select the old and new object (4) press :guilabel:`Replace Geometry` to transfer all the information over."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:217
# 80eef651a11044b185014f4795b8d5ce
msgid "Utilsplugin2 also provides a new selection menu that provides more tools:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:222
# 1139c410c7084e998fb0fe5805c8064c
msgid "These tools have proved to be the most useful:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:224
# 2d959e7f664748d1bbaee9530d01b621
msgid "**Unselect Nodes:**  This tool allows you deselect nodes, which makes it useful for tagging the objects selected.  This tool is necessary if you have mapped several polygon objects with similar attributes and would like to tag the objects without tagging the nodes. To do so, select all of the objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:230
# a186152580da42dba9ffee91fefe488a
msgid "-- polygons, ways and relations -- unselect the nodes and tag appropriately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:236
# 2705aaa4e61d48b6958cb407404a7518
msgid "**Select Last Modified Nodes:**  This tool permits you to go back to the nodes that you most recently changed. It is like undo: node style."
msgstr ""

